        <description>
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Term Type Usage Guide Overview</title>
                <para>
                    This Data Module provides comprehensive guidance for CSDB authors on selecting 
                    the appropriate term type when adding terminology to the AMPEL360 Q100 
                    terminology database. Correct term type classification ensures consistency 
                    across technical publications and enables effective term reuse and cross-referencing.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Purpose:</emphasis> To standardize term type 
                    classification across the Q100 program, supporting accurate terminology 
                    management and S1000D publication generation.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Scope:</emphasis> Covers all 12 term types 
                    defined in KNU-00-00-001-REQ-002 (Term Type Taxonomy Requirements), with 
                    decision criteria, examples, and common mistakes.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Related Documents:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <randomList>
                        <listItem>
                            <para>KNU-00-00-001-REQ-002 — Term Type Taxonomy Requirements</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para>KNU-00-00-001-PUB-001 — Program Glossary DM</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para>KNU-00-00-001-ICD-001 — Terminology Database Schema</para>
                        </listItem>
                    </randomList>
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <!-- SECTION: TERM TYPE TAXONOMY                                     -->
            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Term Type Taxonomy</title>
                <para>
                    The AMPEL360 Q100 terminology database supports 12 distinct term types, 
                    each with specific characteristics and usage patterns. The following sections 
                    provide detailed guidance for each type.
                </para>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>1. NOUN</title>
                    <para id="termtype-noun">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> A word or phrase 
                        that represents a person, place, thing, or concept. Nouns are the most 
                        common term type in technical documentation.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">When to Use:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>Physical components or assemblies (e.g., "Fuel Cell", "Cryogenic Tank")</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Systems or subsystems (e.g., "Propulsion System", "Avionics Suite")</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Materials or substances (e.g., "Liquid Hydrogen", "Composite Material")</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Proper names (e.g., "Q100", "AMPEL360")</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Term</entry>
                                    <entry>Context</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Fuel Cell Stack</entry>
                                    <entry>ATA 71 - Power Plant</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Blended Wing Body</entry>
                                    <entry>ATA 05 - Airframe</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Learning Assurance</entry>
                                    <entry>ATA 95 - AI/ML Systems</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Boil-Off Gas</entry>
                                    <entry>ATA 28 - Fuel System</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Common Mistakes:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>❌ Classifying verb forms as nouns (e.g., "refueling" should be VERB, not NOUN)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>❌ Confusing nouns with concepts (use CONCEPT for abstract ideas)</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>2. VERB</title>
                    <para id="termtype-verb">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> A word that describes 
                        an action, occurrence, or state of being. Verbs are used to document 
                        procedures, processes, and operations.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">When to Use:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>Maintenance actions (e.g., "inspect", "replace", "calibrate")</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>System operations (e.g., "pressurize", "depressurize", "vent")</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Data processing (e.g., "analyze", "compute", "validate")</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Term</entry>
                                    <entry>Context</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>cryocool</entry>
                                    <entry>LH₂ tank thermal management</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>reliquify</entry>
                                    <entry>Boil-off gas recovery</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>inference</entry>
                                    <entry>AI/ML model execution</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>3. ADJECTIVE</title>
                    <para id="termtype-adjective">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> A word that modifies 
                        or describes a noun, providing additional information about its properties 
                        or characteristics.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>"cryogenic" (describing ultra-low temperature conditions)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>"hybrid" (describing dual-mode propulsion)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>"supervised" (describing ML training methodology)</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>4. ADVERB</title>
                    <para id="termtype-adverb">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> A word that modifies 
                        a verb, adjective, or another adverb, typically indicating manner, time, 
                        place, or degree.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>"autonomously" (system operation mode)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>"continuously" (monitoring frequency)</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>5. PHRASE</title>
                    <para id="termtype-phrase">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> A multi-word expression 
                        that functions as a single semantic unit but is not an acronym or abbreviation.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">When to Use:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>Technical terms that cannot be reduced to single words</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Domain-specific expressions with established meaning</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Term</entry>
                                    <entry>Context</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>zero boil-off</entry>
                                    <entry>Cryogenic storage management</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>out-of-distribution detection</entry>
                                    <entry>AI/ML runtime monitoring</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>single source of truth</entry>
                                    <entry>Configuration management</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>6. ACRONYM</title>
                    <para id="termtype-acronym">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> An abbreviation formed 
                        from the initial letters of other words and pronounced as a word (not letter-by-letter).
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Key Distinction:</emphasis> Pronounced as a 
                        word (e.g., "NASA", "RADAR") vs. letter-by-letter (e.g., "XML", "API" — these are ABBREVIATION).
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="3">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Acronym</entry>
                                    <entry>Full Form</entry>
                                    <entry>Pronunciation</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>KNOT</entry>
                                    <entry>Knowledge Nexus of Tangible-uncertainties</entry>
                                    <entry>"not" (as a word)</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>KNU</entry>
                                    <entry>Knowledge Nugget Unit</entry>
                                    <entry>"new" (as a word)</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>SSOT</entry>
                                    <entry>Single Source of Truth</entry>
                                    <entry>"sot" (as a word)</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>7. ABBREVIATION</title>
                    <para id="termtype-abbreviation">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> A shortened form of 
                        a word or phrase, pronounced letter-by-letter or as a contraction.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="3">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Abbreviation</entry>
                                    <entry>Full Form</entry>
                                    <entry>Type</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>LH₂</entry>
                                    <entry>Liquid Hydrogen</entry>
                                    <entry>Chemical notation</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>GH₂</entry>
                                    <entry>Gaseous Hydrogen</entry>
                                    <entry>Chemical notation</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>TBD</entry>
                                    <entry>To Be Determined</entry>
                                    <entry>Letter-by-letter</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>OOD</entry>
                                    <entry>Out-of-Distribution</entry>
                                    <entry>Letter-by-letter</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>8. SYMBOL</title>
                    <para id="termtype-symbol">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> A graphical or 
                        character representation used to denote a specific concept or operation.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Symbol</entry>
                                    <entry>Meaning</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>⚠️</entry>
                                    <entry>Warning indicator</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>≤</entry>
                                    <entry>Less than or equal to</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>∆</entry>
                                    <entry>Delta / change</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>9. FORMULA</title>
                    <para id="termtype-formula">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> A mathematical or 
                        chemical expression representing a relationship or composition.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>2H₂ + O₂ → 2H₂O + Energy (fuel cell reaction)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>E = m × c² (energy-mass equivalence)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>w_i = α × Ê_i + (1 - α) × Î_i (TT allocation formula)</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>10. UNIT</title>
                    <para id="termtype-unit">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> A standard quantity 
                        used to express physical measurements.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="3">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Unit</entry>
                                    <entry>Symbol</entry>
                                    <entry>Measures</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>kilogram</entry>
                                    <entry>kg</entry>
                                    <entry>Mass</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>kelvin</entry>
                                    <entry>K</entry>
                                    <entry>Temperature</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>bar</entry>
                                    <entry>bar</entry>
                                    <entry>Pressure</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>megajoule per kilogram</entry>
                                    <entry>MJ/kg</entry>
                                    <entry>Energy density (mass)</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>11. QUANTITY</title>
                    <para id="termtype-quantity">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> A named physical 
                        property that can be measured (e.g., length, mass, temperature).
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>energy density</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>boil-off rate</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>specific impulse</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>confidence score</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>12. CONCEPT</title>
                    <para id="termtype-concept">
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> An abstract idea, 
                        principle, or methodology that does not fit into other term types.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">When to Use:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>Methodologies and frameworks</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Abstract principles</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Philosophical or theoretical constructs</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100 Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Term</entry>
                                    <entry>Description</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Learning Assurance</entry>
                                    <entry>ML system certification methodology</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Residual Uncertainty</entry>
                                    <entry>Knowledge management metric</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Traceability</entry>
                                    <entry>Requirement tracking principle</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </levelledPara>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <!-- SECTION: DECISION TREE                                          -->
            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Term Type Selection Decision Tree</title>
                <para>
                    Use the following decision tree to determine the appropriate term type:
                </para>
                <para>
                    <sequentialList>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Is it a mathematical or chemical expression?</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ YES: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">FORMULA</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ NO: Continue to step 2</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Is it a graphical symbol or special character?</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ YES: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">SYMBOL</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ NO: Continue to step 3</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Is it a shortened form?</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ YES, pronounced as a word: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">ACRONYM</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ YES, pronounced letter-by-letter or contraction: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">ABBREVIATION</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ NO: Continue to step 4</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Does it measure something?</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ YES, it's a standard of measurement: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">UNIT</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ YES, it's what's being measured: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">QUANTITY</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ NO: Continue to step 5</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">What part of speech is it?</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ Action or process: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">VERB</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ Describes a noun: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">ADJECTIVE</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ Describes a verb/adjective: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">ADVERB</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ Thing, person, or place: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">NOUN</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ Multi-word expression: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">PHRASE</emphasis></para>
                            <para>→ Abstract idea or methodology: Use <emphasis emphasisType="em02">CONCEPT</emphasis></para>
                        </listItem>
                    </sequentialList>
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <!-- SECTION: COMMON MISTAKES                                        -->
            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
