            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <!-- SECTION: SUBMISSION WORKFLOW                                    -->
            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Term Submission Workflow</title>
                <para>
                    Follow these steps when submitting a new term to the terminology database:
                </para>
                <para>
                    <sequentialList>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Step 1: Verify Term Uniqueness</emphasis></para>
                            <para>Search the terminology database to ensure the term doesn't already exist.</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Step 2: Select Term Type</emphasis></para>
                            <para>Use the decision tree in Section 3 to determine the appropriate term type.</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Step 3: Complete Term Record</emphasis></para>
                            <para>Provide all required fields:</para>
                            <para>
                                <randomList>
                                    <listItem><para>Term name (canonical form)</para></listItem>
                                    <listItem><para>Term type (from taxonomy)</para></listItem>
                                    <listItem><para>Definition (clear, concise, unambiguous)</para></listItem>
                                    <listItem><para>Context (ATA chapter, system)</para></listItem>
                                    <listItem><para>Source reference (standard, document, expert)</para></listItem>
                                    <listItem><para>Related terms (synonyms, antonyms, broader/narrower terms)</para></listItem>
                                </randomList>
                            </para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Step 4: Submit for Review</emphasis></para>
                            <para>Submit via terminology database web interface. Terms are reviewed by STK_CM.</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Step 5: Approval and Integration</emphasis></para>
                            <para>Approved terms are automatically exported to CSDB and integrated into publications.</para>
                        </listItem>
                    </sequentialList>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Contact:</emphasis> For questions or assistance, 
                    contact STK_CM via terminology@ampel360.aero.
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <!-- SECTION: S1000D INTEGRATION                                     -->
            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <levelledPara>
                <title>S1000D CSDB Authoring Integration</title>
                <para>
                    When authoring S1000D Data Modules, reference terms from the controlled 
                    terminology using the following markup patterns:
                </para>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>Internal References</title>
                    <para>
                        For terms within the same Data Module:
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
&lt;internalRef internalRefId="term-bwb" 
             internalRefTargetType="irtt01"&gt;BWB&lt;/internalRef&gt;
                        </verbatimText>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>Cross-DM References</title>
                    <para>
                        For terms in the Program Glossary (DMC-AMPEL360-00-00-00-00A-001A-A):
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
&lt;dmRef&gt;
  &lt;dmRefIdent&gt;
    &lt;dmCode modelIdentCode="AMPEL360" 
            systemDiffCode="00" 
            systemCode="00" 
            subSystemCode="0" 
            subSubSystemCode="0" 
            assyCode="00" 
            disassyCode="00" 
            disassyCodeVariant="A" 
            infoCode="001" 
            infoCodeVariant="A" 
            itemLocationCode="A"/&gt;
  &lt;/dmRefIdent&gt;
&lt;/dmRef&gt;
                        </verbatimText>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>Database URI References</title>
                    <para>
                        For direct references to terminology database entries:
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
&lt;externalPubRef&gt;
  &lt;externalPubRefIdent&gt;
    &lt;externalPubCode&gt;ampel360:term:bwb&lt;/externalPubCode&gt;
  &lt;/externalPubRefIdent&gt;
&lt;/externalPubRef&gt;
                        </verbatimText>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <!-- USAGE NOTES                                                     -->
            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Usage Notes</title>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Mandatory Compliance:</emphasis> All CSDB authors 
                    must follow this guidance when adding terms to the terminology database. 
                    Incorrect term type classification may result in publication errors and 
                    inconsistencies.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Updates:</emphasis> This guide is maintained by 
                    STK_CM and updated as the term type taxonomy evolves. Check for the latest 
                    version before submitting new terms.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Training:</emphasis> New CSDB authors should 
                    complete terminology management training before submitting terms. Contact 
                    training@ampel360.aero for course schedules.
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
